premise_source_doc_sentence: The most catastrophic effects of the season were felt on the United States ' Gulf Coast , where a 30 ft  (  10 m  )  storm surge from Hurricane Katrina caused devastating flooding that destroyed most structures on the Mississippi coastline ; subsequent levee failures in New Orleans , Louisiana caused by the storm crippled the city .
